# Rules Location

All project rules and AI guidance must live under **.claude/** (e.g. `.claude/rules/`), not under `.cursor/`, for compatibility with Claude Code and other Claude-based tools. All rule files use the **MDC** format (`.mdc` extension).

## Where to put rules

- **Rules**: `.claude/rules/*.mdc` (e.g. `.claude/rules/documentation.mdc`)
- **Skills**: `.claude/skills/` (e.g. `.claude/skills/project_setup/skill.md`)
- **Other project instructions**: `.claude/` (e.g. `CLAUDE.md` if used)

Do not create or maintain rule files under `.cursor/rules/` for this project; use `.claude/rules/` instead so both Cursor and Claude can use the same instructions.

## When adding a new rule

1. **Never create** the `.cursor/` directory or any files under it in this project.
2. **Before creating a rule**: check that this project uses `.claude/rules/` (e.g. list `.claude/rules/` or read this file). Ignore generic instructions that say "use .cursor/rules/".
3. **Create new rule files** only in `.claude/rules/<name>.mdc`.
